1. Execute smoke testing for VSCT-QA environment. Use config.js
2. For Admin site/Back office scenariors open a new tab and go to new BACK URL
3. Follow steps from test Highlight current scope category
4. Clear cache, clear local storage in browser
5. Open console and keep it open (Webkit browser > Develop > Shown Web Inspector > Console > Errors)
6. After any action fetch errors in console and print if any critical exist
7. Create a report after each section (ID, Title, Result, Detailed error)
8. If the bugs were found create a bug report with Test case ID


